http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Lecturers-principals-seek-parity-in-pay/article13989440.ece

Lecturers and principals of government pre-university colleges have threatened to boycott the ensuing valuation of papers if the State government failed to concede their long-pending demands.The lecturers and principals, under the banner of Core Committee of Karnataka State Pre-University Education Associations, have been demanding implementation of the Kumar Naik committee report on pay parity.Giving details here, Prasad Reddy, president of the district unit of the Principals Association, said that the core committee also met Chief Minister Siddaramaiah in April 2015 and except the assurance, nothing concrete has been done so far to implement the committee report.